<TITLE> Blood test for BCL </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Pabna, April 18 (bdnews24.com)  Aspiring BCL leaders will have to have their blood tested in Pabna from now on. Samsul Haque Tuku, state minister for home affairs and a Pabna MP, said that the obligatory blood test would prevent drug addicts from becoming leaders of the Bangladesh Chhatra League, which is the ruling Awami League's student wing. Candidates for the upcoming Chhatra League's Pabna district council, scheduled on Apr 25, were seen queued up for blood test at the Pabna General Hospital on Sunday. On Sunday, 25 BCL activists had their blood tested. Tuku, explaining the blood test, said that the Awami League wanted the future leadership to be healthy. "We do not want drug addicts." bdnews24.co
